org.semanticweb.rulewerk.rdf

Class RdfModelConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.semanticweb.rulewerk.rdf.RdfModelConverter

  • public final class RdfModelConverter
extends Object
    Class for converting RDF Models to PositiveLiteral sets. Converts each <subject, predicate, object> triple statement of the given rdfModel into an PositiveLiteral of the form TRIPLE(subject, predicate, object). The ternary predicate used for all literals generated from RDF triples is RDF_TRIPLE_PREDICATE_NAME. Subject, predicate and object Values are converted to corresponding Terms:
    • URIs are converted to Constants with the escaped URI String as name.
    • Literals are converted to Constants with names containing the canonical form of the literal label, the data type and the language.
    • BNodes are converted to NamedNulls with the generated blank ID as name. BNodes have unique generated IDs in the context a Models. Blanks with the same name loaded from different models will have different ids.
    Author:
    Irina Dragoste, Markus Kroetzsch

    • Constructor Detail

      • RdfModelConverter

        public RdfModelConverter()
        Construct an object that does not skolemize blank nodes and that uses a ternary predicate named RDF_TRIPLE_PREDICATE_NAME for storing triples.

      • RdfModelConverter

        public RdfModelConverter(boolean skolemize,
                         String triplePredicateName)
        Constructor. If triplePredicateName is a string, then RDF triples will be represented as ternary facts with a predicate of that name. If it is null, then triples will be converted to binary facts where the predicate is the RDF predicate; moreover, triples with rdf:rype as predicate will be converted to unary facts.
        Parameters:
        skolemize - if true, blank nodes are translated to constants with generated IRIs; otherwise they are replanced by named nulls with generated ids
        triplePredicateName - name of the ternary predicate that should be used to store RDF triples; or null to generate binary predicates from the predicates of RDF triples

    • Method Detail

      • rdfModelToFacts

        public Set<Fact> rdfModelToFacts(org.openrdf.model.Model model)
        Converts each <subject, predicate, object> triple statement of the given rdfModel into a Fact of the form TRIPLE(subject, predicate, object). See RDF_TRIPLE_PREDICATE_NAME, the ternary predicate name used for all literals generated from RDF triples.
        Parameters:
        model - a Model of an RDF document, containing triple statements that will be converter to facts.
        Returns:
        a set of facts corresponding to the statements of given rdfModel.
